66 to receive such grants in accordance with this part.
67 (c) The Georgia Student Finance Authority may contract with a grant coordinating
68 organization authorized to do business in this state to implement and administer the
69 Georgia Foster Care Scholarship program; provided, however, that such contract shall
70 require the grant coordinating organization to ensure that 100 percent of funds appropriated
71 for such program shall be expended on grants to eligible students.
72 (d) The Georgia Student Finance Authority is authorized to define such terms and
