75 20-3-673.
76 (a) Subject to appropriations made specifically for the purposes of this part, to receive a
77 Georgia Foster Care Scholarship, an eligible student shall:
78 (1) Complete a simplified application process established by the Georgia Student
79 Finance Authority, which shall include completion of the Free Application for Federal
80 Student Aid (FAFSA) to determine the level of need and eligibility for state and federal
81 financial aid programs;
82 (2) Remain in good standing with the eligible postsecondary institution in which he or
83 she is enrolled or to which he or she has been accepted for admission;
84 (3) Maintain satisfactory academic progress in accordance with the standards and
85 practices used for federal Title IV programs by the eligible postsecondary institution at
86 which the student is enrolled; and
87 (4) Comply with the rules, regulations, and procedures prescribed by the Georgia Student
88 Finance Authority in accordance with this part.
89 (b) The total per-semester amount of a Georgia Foster Care Scholarship awarded to each
90 eligible student shall not exceed the costs of the eligible student's tuition, room, board, meal
